    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose Band 3 observations of the Hubble Frontier Field galaxy cluster Abell 2744 in order to study the molecular gas properties of faint high-redshift galaxies via their CO emission. Gravitational lensing by the cluster magnifies the flux of background sources enabling source detections with far lower integration times than otherwise possible. Abell 2744 is one of the most promising and well-studied lensing clusters and is ideal for a pilot ALMA early science program.</prp:abstract>
